'''''Robin of Sherlock''''' is a 1985 [[adventure game]] developed by [[Delta 4]] and published by Silversoft.<ref name="WOSREF">{{cite web | url=http://www.worldofspectrum.org/infoseek.cgi?regexp=^Robin+of+Sherlock$&pub=^Silversoft+Ltd$&loadpics=1 | title=Robin of Sherlock | publisher=World of Spectrum | accessdate=2014-06-21 }}</ref> It parodies the earlier games ''[[The Hobbit (1982 video game)|The Hobbit]]'' and ''[[Sherlock (video game)|Sherlock]]''. It was written using ''[[The Quill Adventure System|The Quill]]''.

The game mixes the universes of [[Robin Hood]] and Sherlock Holmes with a number of characters from other media, including [[Smurfs]], Dorothy from [[The Wonderful Wizard of Oz|The Wizard of Oz]], [[Red Riding Hood]], [[Goldilocks]], and others.<ref>[http://oldwww.nvg.ntnu.no/sinclair/industry/publishers/delta4_su1285.htm Bored out of his mind]. [[Sinclair User]], 1985</ref> It also involves [[Professor Moriarty]] masquerading as [[Herne the Hunter]].

